org.ndnx.ndn.io.content
Class Collection

All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
ACL, NameEnumerationResponse.NameEnumerationResponseMessage
public class Collection
extends GenericXMLEncodable
implements XMLEncodable, Iterable<Link>, Cloneable

A representation of a collection of NDN objects, represented as a list of Link s. See Link for a discussion of what such links can refer to and their security. A Collection is the easiest way in NDN of representing extensional containment -- a fixed list of items that form a group, where it is possible to say that an item is either in or out of the group. Containment in NDN can also be represented intentionally -- by looking at the set of children a given name currently has. In that latter case, it is impossible to say in general whether something is not in the set, as there might exist a child with that name, but it is not accessible to your network at the moment. By tailoring the meaning of and labels attached to the Links in a Collection, one can generate special-purpose Collection subclasses with particular semantics, useful in particular applications. See ACL and the Name Enumeration protocol for examples of this.

Decode this object during an ongoing decoding pass; this is what subclasses generally need to know how to implement.
